    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="740"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Pearson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 62.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 121, of the 7th ultimo, in relation to the protection of witnesses
                    in the Labaree case, and to commend the attitude taken in your note in which you
                    requested the Persian Government to protect the said witnesses.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—Subsequent correspondence will be printed in
                            <ref target="frus1906p1">Foreign Relations, 1906</ref>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
